This paper deals with deep learning and convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for image classification tasks, which are typically categorized under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the architecture and training of neural networks, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper explores the interpretability and analysis of the models, which can be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational linguistics (cs.CL).
